[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6372,
        "end_time": 9415,
        "text": "If you tried to pay for something\nwith a piece of paper,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9439,
        "end_time": 11350,
        "text": "you might run into some trouble."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11374,
        "end_time": 15311,
        "text": "Unless, of course, the piece of paper\nwas a hundred dollar bill."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 15335,
        "end_time": 18890,
        "text": "But what is it that makes that bill\nso much more interesting and valuable"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 18914,
        "end_time": 20769,
        "text": "than other pieces of paper?"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 20793,
        "end_time": 23421,
        "text": "After all, there&#39;s not much\nyou can do with it."
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 23445,
        "end_time": 25055,
        "text": "You can&#39;t eat it."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 25079,
        "end_time": 26556,
        "text": "You can&#39;t build things with it."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 26580,
        "end_time": 28272,
        "text": "And burning it is actually illegal."
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 29089,
        "end_time": 30460,
        "text": "So what&#39;s the big deal?"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 30770,
        "end_time": 32991,
        "text": "Of course, you probably know the answer."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 33015,
        "end_time": 35410,
        "text": "A hundred dollar bill\nis printed by the government"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 35434,
        "end_time": 37460,
        "text": "and designated as official currency,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 37484,
        "end_time": 39511,
        "text": "while other pieces of paper are not."
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 40384,
        "end_time": 42332,
        "text": "But that&#39;s just what makes them legal."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 42356,
        "end_time": 45261,
        "text": "What makes a hundred dollar bill\nvaluable, on the other hand,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 45285,
        "end_time": 47546,
        "text": "is how many or few of them are around."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 48031,
        "end_time": 51472,
        "text": "Throughout history, most currency,\nincluding the US dollar,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 51496,
        "end_time": 53499,
        "text": "was linked to valuable commodities"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 53523,
        "end_time": 55352,
        "text": "and the amount of it in circulation"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 55376,
        "end_time": 58372,
        "text": "depended on a government&#39;s gold\nor silver reserves."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 59166,
        "end_time": 61930,
        "text": "But after the US abolished\nthis system in 1971,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 61954,
        "end_time": 65762,
        "text": "the dollar became\nwhat is known as fiat money,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 65786,
        "end_time": 68197,
        "text": "meaning not linked\nto any external resource"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 68221,
        "end_time": 71159,
        "text": "but relying instead solely\non government policy"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 71183,
        "end_time": 73620,
        "text": "to decide how much currency to print."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 73644,
        "end_time": 76582,
        "text": "Which branch of our government\nsets this policy?"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 76606,
        "end_time": 79572,
        "text": "The Executive, the Legislative,\nor the Judicial?"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 79596,
        "end_time": 82044,
        "text": "The surprising answer is:\nnone of the above!"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 82068,
        "end_time": 86801,
        "text": "In fact, monetary policy is set\nby an independent Federal Reserve System,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 86825,
        "end_time": 88552,
        "text": "or the Fed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 88576,
        "end_time": 92595,
        "text": "made up of 12 regional banks\nin major cities around the country."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 92619,
        "end_time": 93930,
        "text": "Its board of governors,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 93954,
        "end_time": 96979,
        "text": "which is appointed by the president\nand confirmed by the Senate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 97003,
        "end_time": 98097,
        "text": "reports to Congress,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 98121,
        "end_time": 101595,
        "text": "and all the Fed&#39;s profit\ngoes into the US Treasury."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 101619,
        "end_time": 103572,
        "text": "But to keep the Fed from being influenced"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 103596,
        "end_time": 105762,
        "text": "by the day-to-day\nvicissitudes of politics,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 105786,
        "end_time": 109238,
        "text": "it is not under the direct control\nof any branch of government."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 109262,
        "end_time": 112678,
        "text": "Why doesn&#39;t the Fed just decide\nto print infinite hundred dollar bills"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 112702,
        "end_time": 114227,
        "text": "to make everyone happy and rich?"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 114251,
        "end_time": 116871,
        "text": "Well, because then the bills\nwouldn&#39;t be worth anything."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 116895,
        "end_time": 118996,
        "text": "Think about the purpose of currency,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 119020,
        "end_time": 121832,
        "text": "which is to be exchanged\nfor goods and services."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 121856,
        "end_time": 124047,
        "text": "If the total amount\nof currency in circulation"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 124071,
        "end_time": 128794,
        "text": "increases faster than the total value\nof goods and services in the economy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 128818,
        "end_time": 130675,
        "text": "then each individual piece will be able"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 130699,
        "end_time": 133342,
        "text": "to buy a smaller portion\nof those things than before."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 133366,
        "end_time": 135204,
        "text": "This is called inflation."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 135228,
        "end_time": 136652,
        "text": "On the other hand,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 136676,
        "end_time": 138438,
        "text": "if the money supply remains the same,"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 138462,
        "end_time": 140594,
        "text": "while more goods\nand services are produced,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 140618,
        "end_time": 142564,
        "text": "each dollar&#39;s value would increase"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 142588,
        "end_time": 144817,
        "text": "in a process known as deflation."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 144841,
        "end_time": 146616,
        "text": "So which is worse?"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 146640,
        "end_time": 147823,
        "text": "Too much inflation"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 147847,
        "end_time": 151133,
        "text": "means that the money in your wallet today\nwill be worth less tomorrow,"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 151157,
        "end_time": 153156,
        "text": "making you want to spend it right away."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 153180,
        "end_time": 157013,
        "text": "While this would stimulate business,\nit would also encourage overconsumption,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 157037,
        "end_time": 159875,
        "text": "or hoarding commodities,\nlike food and fuel,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 159899,
        "end_time": 161620,
        "text": "raising their prices"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 161644,
        "end_time": 164481,
        "text": "and leading to consumer shortages\nand even more inflation."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 165704,
        "end_time": 169096,
        "text": "But deflation would make people\nwant to hold onto their money,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 169120,
        "end_time": 171009,
        "text": "and a decrease in consumer spending"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 171033,
        "end_time": 172567,
        "text": "would reduce business profits,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 172591,
        "end_time": 175930,
        "text": "leading to more unemployment\nand a further decrease in spending,"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 175954,
        "end_time": 178227,
        "text": "causing the economy to keep shrinking."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 178251,
        "end_time": 181894,
        "text": "So most economists believe that\nwhile too much of either is dangerous,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 181918,
        "end_time": 186806,
        "text": "a small, consistent amount of inflation\nis necessary to encourage economic growth."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 187787,
        "end_time": 190234,
        "text": "The Fed uses vast amounts of economic data"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 190258,
        "end_time": 193597,
        "text": "to determine how much currency\nshould be in circulation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 193621,
        "end_time": 195575,
        "text": "including previous rates of inflation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 195599,
        "end_time": 197881,
        "text": "international trends,\nand the unemployment rate."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 198739,
        "end_time": 200443,
        "text": "Like in the story of Goldilocks,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 200467,
        "end_time": 202325,
        "text": "they need to get the numbers just right"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 202349,
        "end_time": 204921,
        "text": "in order to stimulate growth\nand keep people employed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 204945,
        "end_time": 207670,
        "text": "without letting inflation\nreach disruptive levels."
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 207694,
        "end_time": 209044,
        "text": "The Fed not only determines"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 209068,
        "end_time": 212219,
        "text": "how much that paper\nin your wallet is worth"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 212243,
        "end_time": 214962,
        "text": "but also your chances\nof getting or keeping the job"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 214986,
        "end_time": 216325,
        "text": "where you earn it."
    }
]